\subsubsection{Results}

In Figure \ref{timelengthavg} the average search times and average trajectory lengths of the runs of the test series are shown. 

The average search time of intelligent search system was about 30\% lower than the average search time of the uninformed search system and the difference between the systems is even higher in the trajectory length, with the intelligent search system traveling nearly 40\% less distance. The reason for the greater difference in the trajectory length is that the switching of high-level tasks and the peek tasks take some time (about 5 seconds per high level task switch and about 20 seconds per peek task). This happens more often with the intelligent search system and during this time the robot stays at the same position. The variance in the search runs was high, therefore the search times and trajectory lengths are shown in more detail in Figure \ref{search times}.
